(10355, 909, 'team_0_bio', 'A millennium, no, 15 years ago, Julie Fairchild and I separately went on our own and, since days alone can get long, thought we might share an office.  The physical office space never materialized, but inside a year, an LLP did.\r\n \r\nIn that company of two, I expected we’d attract employees on their way to bigger things. What did I know? Our niche work is far more than widgets, and Lovell-Fairchild grew into an enviable team of professionals whom we\'ve seen grow into experts in what they do. \r\n \r\nIn our strategic-communications work, I lean into the communications part, urging our team, on one level, to spell canceled with one l, and, regardless of AP Stylebook, to use “hopefully” to mean what it says. More generally, in framing, messaging, media training, writing, pitches . . . I help shape client needs into news.'),
(10356, 909, '_team_0_bio', 'field_5931ba112e426'),
(10357, 909, 'team_1_image', '903'),
(10358, 909, '_team_1_image', 'field_58be26dbd5a67'),
