(15933, 1005, '_testimonial_slides_7_content', 'field_595d61a30fa56'),
(15934, 1005, 'testimonial_slides_7_author', 'Tom Tradup,<br> V.P./News & Talk Programming. SALEM Radio Network™'),
(15935, 1005, '_testimonial_slides_7_author', 'field_595d634685188'),
(15936, 1005, 'testimonial_slides_8_content', 'Lovell-Fairchild Communications is ALL IN for their clients. They are not only responsive, but are pro-active. They come to you with the idea first, where other firms typically ride the wave you have already generated for yourself and just manage what the client already does. <br><br>\r\n\r\nLovell-Fairchild takes the time to learn the client\'s voice. So many times we have encountered square pegs and round holes. They realize there is not one size fits all, and while they will educate you and try to take you places you haven’t gone before, they will not set you up for failure. In my experience, and we have had many, there hasn’t been an equal that we have worked with.'),
(15937, 1005, '_testimonial_slides_8_content', 'field_595d61a30fa56'),
(15938, 1005, 'testimonial_slides_8_author', 'Sandy Parker,<br> Executive Producer Four Blood Moons'),
(15939, 1005, '_testimonial_slides_8_author', 'field_595d634685188'),
(15940, 1005, 'testimonial_slides_9_content', 'From the start of our work together, Lovell-Fairchild thought with us, and often ahead of us. We valued their connections, ideas, organization, teamwork . . . and, of course, the media coverage.'),
