(383, 1, '2017-04-14 18:23:21', '2017-04-14 18:23:21', 'After a disastrous debut on the pro circuit, a young golfer finds himself unexpectedly stranded in Utopia, Texas and welcomed by an eccentric rancher.', 'Seven Days In Utopia', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'seven-days-in-utopia', '', '', '2017-07-12 17:45:34', '2017-07-12 17:45:34', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=383', 150, 'clients', '', 0),
(384, 1, '2017-04-14 18:25:25', '2017-04-14 18:25:25', 'Tough-as-steel Seth McArdle is a high school senior who fixes cars to pay the rent and is raising his little sisters alone in Sinai, Texas—a former oil town whose only green patch lies between the field goal posts. A run-in with the football star lands Seth in a month of after-school work, facing Abel, part-time groundskeeper, and a looming deadline to prepare the field for homecoming.\r\n\r\nSeth is angry, and Abel is secretive. Day after day the two work at cross-purposes, until the day Abel steps up for Seth, and in the new trust that forms, becomes Seth’s mentor. When Seth learns that his father has died, his home will be auctioned, and the girls must go to distant relatives, he turns to Abel—and finds him skipping town.\r\n\r\nAdd Abel now to letdowns in Seth’s life. Add desperation-fueled crime to the setbacks Seth’s heading into. What is Abel’s secret, and why does it hobble him when Seth needs him most? Can Seth see past disappointment and do the right thing? Can two wounded men face their pasts with forgiveness and find the redemption they crave?\r\n\r\nIt’s almost homecoming in Sinai.', 'Abel\'s Field', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'abels-field', '', '', '2017-07-12 20:16:23', '2017-07-12 20:16:23', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=384', 271, 'clients', '', 0),
(385, 1, '2017-04-14 18:26:04', '2017-04-14 18:26:04', 'Applying Biblical Principles to Work, Wealth and the World\r\n\r\nFrom author, teacher and Christian apologist R.C. Sproul Jr. comes ECONOMICS FOR EVERYBODY, a 12-part DVD series that combines biblical truth with economic principles to help Christians be better stewards of the world they have been given.\r\n\r\nFeaturing insightful, easy-to-follow instruction from R.C. Sproul Jr. and often-humorous, often-stirring footage from old films and newsreels, ECONOMICS FOR EVERYBODY makes learning the principles, practices and consequences of this vital topic fun and enlightening.\r\n\r\nVisit', 'Economics For Everybody By R.C. Sproul Jr.', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'economics-for-everybody-by-r-c-sproul-jr', '', '', '2017-07-12 17:59:15', '2017-07-12 17:59:15', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=385', 330, 'clients', '', 0),
(386, 1, '2017-04-14 18:27:20', '2017-04-14 18:27:20', 'Where fates collide, one road appears.\r\n\r\nFueled by revenge, Michael (Philip Bulcock) sets up a meeting at an out-of-the-way diner with the man who murdered his wife and child six years earlier. But his plans of killing him come to a sudden standstill when two gunmen burst in to rob the place. Michael takes matters into his own hands, shooting a robber and holding the entire diner hostage until the man he really wants to target arrives. In the midst of all these events, Michael finds an unlikely ally in Don (Kim Estes), a devout Christian who believes God is going to help him in his endeavor. While Michael battles with his faith, the hostages begin to find extraordinary connections between them. CROSSROAD is an emotional and inspiring story of redemption, forgiveness and the ultimate realization of God\'s grace at work in every life.', 'Crossroad', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'crossroad__trashed', '', '', '2017-07-12 20:16:56', '2017-07-12 20:16:56', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=386', 48, 'clients', '', 0),
(387, 1, '2017-04-14 18:27:49', '2017-04-14 18:27:49', 'After his own alcohol abuse caused him to lose everything—job, family, hope—Dick Wallrath found faith, and with it the strength to realize that a strong family and the love of his children were the truest measures of success.\r\n\r\nWith his sons, Dick went on to build a thriving business and used that success to become the highest all-time individual donor in Texas to 4-H and FFA through his educational scholarships.\r\n\r\nBased on this true story, DEEP IN THE HEART is a tale of finding lost faith, love of family and, ultimately, redemption. Faith brings second chances and opportunities to do great things. Dick Wallrath’s story proves hope can reach DEEP IN THE HEART.', 'Deep In The Heart', '', 'trash', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'deep-in-the-heart__trashed', '', '', '2017-07-12 20:16:56', '2017-07-12 20:16:56', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=387', 50, 'clients', '', 0),
(394, 1, '2017-04-14 21:45:36', '2017-04-14 21:45:36', 'June Hunt, MA, is the founder of HOPE FOR THE HEART, a worldwide biblical counseling ministry that provides resources on 100 different topics. She presents God’s Truth for Today’s Problems on two daily broadcasts reaching an estimated audience of nearly 1.5 million people. The daily half-hour program, HOPE FOR THE HEART, and the live 2-hour call-in counseling program, HOPE IN THE NIGHT, represent coverage on approximately 250 stations across the nation. June Hunt has taught internationally on seminary campuses, has been a Bible school adjunct professor, and has led Bible studies and conferences for over 30 years.\r\n\r\nJune Hunt’s Biblical Counseling Library, with its foundation based in the truths of Scripture, covers 100 topics. Her books include: The Answer to Anger, The Biblical Counseling Reference Guide, Bonding with Your Child through Boundaries, Bonding with Your Teen through Boundaries, Caring for a Loved One with Cancer, Counseling Through Your Bible Handbook, Hope for Your Heart, How to Deal with Difficult Relationships, How to Defeat Harmful Habits, How to Forgive ... When You Don’t Feel Like It, How to Handle Your Emotions, How to Rise Above Abuse, and Seeing Yourself Through God’s Eyes.\r\n\r\nSeveral of June’s works have been translated into over 30 languages, and HOPE FOR THE HEART’s ministry extends around the world in over 60 countries on 6 continents.', 'Hope For The Heart, June Hunt', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hope-for-the-heart-june-hunt', '', '', '2017-06-01 22:21:07', '2017-06-01 22:21:07', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=394', 78, 'clients', '', 0),
(395, 1, '2017-04-14 21:46:19', '2017-04-14 21:46:19', '<div>For small and medium size business owners and their leadership, Bobby Albert is a trusted advisor that empowers transformative business growth by helping leaders build value-driven cultures where people thrive and profits soar.</div>\r\n<div>He is unlike other leadership experts who provide traditional leadership advice relating to skills primarily for large company executives.</div>', 'Values-Driven Leadership', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'values-driven-leadership', '', '', '2017-06-01 22:21:08', '2017-06-01 22:21:08', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=395', 193, 'clients', '', 0),
