(437, 1, '2017-04-14 22:41:53', '2017-04-14 22:41:53', 'WORLD PREMIERE OF FAMILY COMEDY ‘MOMS’ NIGHT OUT’\r\n\r\nTUESDAY, APRIL 29, 2014\r\n\r\nWHAT: MOMS’ NIGHT OUT – World Premiere\r\n\r\nAward-winning stars of film and television walk the red carpet at the world premiere of the anticipated family comedy MOMS’ NIGHT OUT featuring two-time Emmy winner Patricia Heaton. The laugh-out-loud look at moms, dads, kids, love and marriage is executive produced by Heaton (Everybody Loves Raymond, The Middle) and her husband and co-star David Hunt, and is directed by Jon and Andrew Erwin.\r\n\r\nWHO: Cast members Patricia Heaton (Emmy Winner, Everybody Loves Raymond), Sarah Drew (Grey’s Anatomy), Sean Astin (THE LORD OF THE RINGS), Trace Adkins (Platinum-selling Country music artist), Harry Shum, Jr. (Glee), Andrea Logan White (REVELATION ROAD), Abbie Cobb (The Secret Life of the American Teenager), Anjelah Johnson (Comedian, ENOUGH SAID), Kevin Downes (COURAGEOUS), Robert Amaya (COURAGEOUS), Alex Kendrick (COURAGEOUS), Sammi Hanratty (The Unit). Executive Producer David Hunt, Co-Director Jon Erwin, Co-Director Andy Erwin. And other guests including Cuba Gooding, Jr. (Academy Award ® Winner JERRY MAGUIRE, MEN OF HONOR), Kevin Sorbo (Hercules the Lengendary Journeys), Kirk Cameron (Fireproof)\r\n\r\nMore talent to be confirmed…\r\n\r\nWHEN:\r\n\r\nTuesday, April 29\r\n\r\n5:30 p.m. – Press check-in\r\n\r\n6:00-7:00 p.m. – Red Carpet\r\n\r\nWHERE:\r\n\r\nTCL Chinese Theater\r\n\r\n6925 Hollywood Blvd\r\n\r\nHollywood, Calif. 90028', 'Moms\' Night Out L.A. Premiere - Chinese Theater', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'moms-night-out-l-a-premiere-chinese-theater', '', '', '2017-07-12 16:34:37', '2017-07-12 16:34:37', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=437', 110, 'clients', '', 0),
(438, 1, '2017-04-14 22:42:42', '2017-04-14 22:42:42', 'SAN ANTONIO – Jan. 4, 2013 – Dr. James Dobson’s BUILDING A FAMILY LEGACY conference comes to San Antonio—the place where it all began 35 years before—Saturday, Jan. 19, at Cornerstone Church. The one-day event—which is free with reserved tickets (www.buildingafamilylegacy.com)—offers parents vital insight into biblical principles for raising godly families and affecting generations to come.\r\n\r\n“I’m looking forward to being back in San Antonio where God blessed this message years ago,” Dr. Dobson said. “Now, with the experience of raising children behind me, and the glory of grandchildren before me, I have a broadened perspective and new insights I’m eager to share with today’s parents and grandparents.”\r\n\r\nBUILDING A FAMILY LEGACY has deep San Antonio roots. In 1978, Dr. Dobson presented a seminar at Laurie Auditorium that he titled Focus on the Family, and video cameras ran. That series was eventually seen by 80 million people around the world and launched his national ministry. Now, BUILDING A FAMILY LEGACY offers fresh insight on timeless principles encouraging parents and grandparents to make a lasting difference. Session topics from Dr. Dobson include Legacy, Bringing Up Boys and Bringing Up Girls.\r\n\r\nThe BUILDING A FAMILY LEGACY event begins with an optional complimentary continental breakfast at 7:30 a.m., with doors for the conference opening at 8 a.m. The event, which concludes at 1:30 p.m., also includes complimentary lunch, and child care is provided (reservations needed).', 'Building A Family Legacy With Dr. James Dobson - San Antonio', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'building-a-family-legacy-with-dr-james-dobson-san-antonio', '', '', '2017-07-12 17:58:30', '2017-07-12 17:58:30', '', 0, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//?post_type=clients&#038;p=438', 310, 'clients', '', 0),
