(672, 1, '2017-04-21 19:07:49', '2017-04-21 19:07:49', 'Before she succumbs to cancer, the dying wish of Laura Mayfield-Bennett is to be reunited with the daughter she never knew. Unfortunately, that daughter, Katie Lapp, is a member of the Amish order. Katie is about to be married, but uneasy about the path ahead. Now she discovers the secret her parents have kept from her: she\'s adopted.\n\nThe film is based on the celebrated first novel of the best-selling "The Heritage of Lancaster County" book series from author Beverly Lewis. Stars Danielle Panabaker &amp; Sherry Stringfield.', 'The Shunning', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '372-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-04-21 19:07:49', '2017-04-21 19:07:49', '', 372, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//2017/04/21/372-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(673, 1, '2017-07-12 23:01:55', '2017-07-12 23:01:55', 'Normajean Honsberger\'s battle with cancer ended May 2, 2000. Diagnoses with breast cancer in 1992, she lost her husband, Al, to lung cancer in the midst of her own struggle. But Normajean didn\'t give up. She said, "God doesn\'t ask of me something He hasn\'s empowered me to do...I can\'t change my circumstance. The only control I have is how I respond to them. I choose joy!" As an ordained minister, she taught each Sunday and believed God\'s promis that she would not just have life but "have it more abundantly." This book is a compilation of her sermon series on the book of Philippians that earned her the title "Captain Joy."', 'Will You Choose Joy?', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '339-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-07-12 23:01:56', '2017-07-12 23:01:56', '', 339, 'http://lovell-fairchild.dev//2017/04/21/339-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
